For eight years, they gave Obama, Biden, and Hillary tons of criticism for things like Fast and Furious and Benghazi. And I will argue that a lot of it was deserved. As a libertarian conservative, I disagreed with a great deal of Obama's foreign and domestic policies. There were plenty of times that Congress had a right and an obligation to investigate the Executive Branch. And I gave the Republicans the benefit of the doubt that those decision were based on honest disagreements of policy and direction.
But now, I must admit that I was wrong. I was wrong -- totally and completely.
The fact that nearly every Republican in Congress -- save but for Mitt Romney (with a growing level of scorn for the president) and Justin Amash (who is no longer a Republican) -- the rest of the party is giving Trump a pass on his policies (I use the term as loosely as one can) and his erratic mental/emotional behaviour.
